commit.message:
libmx5000: Use device ids for HID proxuy mode instead of receiver ids

Use the wireless-product-id of the device behind the receiver for
HID proxy mode instead of the USB product-id of the receiver.

This aligns the libmx5000 product-id usage with the udev rules
and LCDd-hwdetect product-id usage from lcdproc.

Signed-off-by: Hans de Goede <hdegoede@redhat.com>

libmx5000: Add hidraw_lib.c helper library, re-open hidraw device on connection loss

Add a hidraw_lib.c helper library doing most of the hidraw stuff, modelled
after hidraw_lib.c from lcdproc.

The main new features this brings is automatic re-opening of the hidraw device
on connection loss.

Signed-off-by: Hans de Goede <hdegoede@redhat.com>

libmx5000: Switch to hidraw interface

Switch to using the modern hidraw interface for accessing HID devices
from userspace, this make libmx5000 / mx5000-tool also work when the
keyboard is paired over Bluetooth, rather then used with the receiver
in HID proxy mode.

Signed-off-by: Hans de Goede <hdegoede@redhat.com>
